<item>
            <title>[FLINK-8676] Memory Leak in AbstractKeyedStateBackend.applyToAllKeys() when backend is base on RocksDB</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-8676</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;`AbstractKeyedStateBackend.applyToAllKeys() ` uses backend&apos;s getKeys(stateName, namespace) to get all keys that belong to `namespace`. But, in `RocksDBKeyedStateBackend.getKeys()` if just return a object which wrap a `rocksdb iterator`, that is dangous, because rocksdb will ping the resources that belong to the iterator into memory untill iterator.close() is invoked, but it didn&apos;t invoked right now. This will lead to memory leak finally.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
