&lt;p&gt;    This PR addressed issue &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-8676&quot; title=&quot;Memory Leak in AbstractKeyedStateBackend.applyToAllKeys() when backend is base on RocksDB&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-8676&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-8676&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;(&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-8676&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-8676&lt;/a&gt;). `AbstractKeyedStateBackend.applyToAllKeys() ` uses backend&apos;s `getKeys(stateName, namespace)` to get all keys that belong to `namespace`. But, in `RocksDBKeyedStateBackend.getKeys()` if just return a object which wrap a `rocksdb iterator`, that is dangous, because rocksdb will ping the resources that belong to the iterator into memory till `iterator.close()` is invoked, but it wasn&apos;t invoked right now. This could lead to memory leak finally.&lt;/p&gt;

